Bus fire kills 19 Pakistanis in Iran 
Eighteen Pakistani women and a young girl were killed when the bus in
which they were travelling caught fire in western Iran, the Kayhan
newspaper reported here Monday.
Five Pakistanis suffered serious burns in the fire Sunday in the city
of Malayer in Hamedan province.
The victims were among 58 Pakistani pilgrims on their way back from the
holy city of Qom, in central Iran.
The paper did not say what caused the fire.
